  "img": "icons/creatures/abilities/dragon-breath-purple.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>The feral power within you increases, your Form of the Beast natural weapons can now deal Force damage instead if you wish.</p><p>You can also alter your form to help you adapt to your surroundings. When you finish a Short or Long Rest, choose one of the following benefits, which lasts until you finish your next Short or Long Rest:</p><p><strong>Climbing</strong>. You gain a Climb Speed equal to your Speed, and you can climb difficult surfaces, including upside down on ceilings, without needing to make an ability check.</p><p><strong>Flying</strong>. <em>Requires 17th level in Barbarian.</em> You gain the ability to sprout a pair wings from your back, gaining a Fly Speed equal your Speed.</p><p>You cannot manifest your wings while wearing armor unless the armor is made to accommodate them, and clothing not made to accommodate your wings might be destroyed when you manifest them.</p><p><strong>Jumping</strong>. When you jump, you can make a Strength (Athletics) check and extend your jump by a number of feet equal to the check's total. You can make this special check only once per turn.</p><p><strong>Swimming</strong>. You gain a Swim Speed equal to your Speed, and you can breathe underwater.</p><section id=\"secret-fmUsdHfrCcgOKhoH\" class=\"secret\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>This feature includes Active Effects for each option which you can activate accordingly with each rest.</p></section>",
